article.description: — Diego Campisano scored 18 points and Trent McLaughlin had a go-ahead layup with 22 seconds remaining to rally Northern Arizona to a 74-73 victory over North Dakota on Saturday night.
article.headline: Campisano, McLaughlin rally Northern Arizona to 74-73 victory over North Dakota
article.linkText: Campisano, McLaughlin rally Northern Arizona to 74-73 victory over North Dakota
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- — Diego Campisano scored 18 points and Trent McLaughlin had a go-ahead layup with 22 seconds remaining to rally Northern Arizona to a 74-73 victory over North Dakota on Saturday night. Campisano shot 7 for 10, including 2 for 4 from beyond the arc for the Lumberjacks (7-8). McLaughlin scored 17 points, going 5 of 14 from the floor, including 4 for 10 from 3-point range, and 3 for 6 from the line. Carson Basham had 13 points and shot 5 of 9 from the field and 3 for 4 from the line. B.J. Omot led the Fightin' Hawks (8-9) in scoring, finishing with 15 points and seven rebounds. Treysen Eaglestaff added 14 points and four assists for North Dakota. Tsotne Tsartsidze also had 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
